# Top-level production dependencies — human-edited source.
#
# requirements.txt is the fully-pinned lockfile that should be regenerated
# from this file. Workflow:
#
#   # add or change a dep here, then:
#   pip-compile --resolver=backtracking requirements.in -o requirements.txt
#
# To pick up upstream security fixes:
#   pip-compile --upgrade requirements.in -o requirements.txt
#
# Dev tools (ruff/mypy/pytest-cov/types-requests/pip-audit/pre-commit) live in
# requirements-dev.in and only get installed in CI / local dev. They are kept
# out of the runtime image to keep the production image small.

